-- Copper in London Declines for a Third Day to Two-Week Low at $6,470/Ton
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-07-19T00:04:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/copper-in-london-declines-for-a-third-day-to-two-week-low-at-6-470-ton.html

          
          
             Copper in London dropped for a third
day to the lowest level in two weeks. The contract for delivery
in three months on the London Metal Exchange fell as much as 0.2
percent to $6,470 a metric ton, before trading at $6,480 a ton
by 8:04 a.m. in Singapore.  
          
          


  


        